The paper focuses on the task of super-resolution in the context of mobile devices, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves model compression techniques and optimization of processing speed, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of heterogeneous mobile processors, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and augmented reality (cs.AR) applications.
